<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-20T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-20T16:30:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/26: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay (<persName type="from">Wright</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-20T18:00:00-03:30">July 20,
                                    1932—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>44. Uruguayan press today carries Department’s announcement to the press
                            regarding extension of our good offices. The delicacy of the situation
                            arising from the change in attitude of the Argentine Government, of
                            which <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bliss</persName> has kept me closely
                            informed, has rendered it advisable for me to limit my reply to all
                            press inquiries here: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I have as yet received no official information that my
                                    Government has made such an announcement to the press.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>